Name: Punto de Acogida del Camino del Cid de Valdanzo
Place list: ['Shelter in Spain', 'Shelter in Castile and león', 'Shelter in Soria']
Description: Hall of the town hall of about 120 square meters. It has no beds or bunk beds. Space for sleeping bag and sleeping bag is given. It has 2 toilets, one for ladies and one for gentlemen. Without shower. The city council gives a plot to camp. It is a meadow that is next to the river. In the meadow there are tables and chairs where you can sit. Also a source with drinking water. Fire is not allowed in the area. Regardless of whether it is a camping area, you must notify in advance.
